Cook penne according to package directions. Drain and set aside. Meanwhile, in a 4-quart saucepan, heat tomatoes, tomato sauce and wine; allow to simmer while cooking the veal. In a nonstick skillet, heat olive oil; add garlic and ground veal. Saut√© until veal is cooked. Drain excess fat; pat veal with paper towels to remove any remaining fat. Add veal to sauce. Season with basil, salt and pepper. Divide penne into individual bowls; top with sauce.